<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-05T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="899" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d899">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/576b: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-05T13:00:00-04:00">April 5,
                                1943—1 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2124. From the Under Secretary. Secretary Morgenthau asked me to let you
                        know, in reply to your message<note n="28" xml:id="d899fn28">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> which he received this morning,
                        that in view of the publication he is having a press conference at 3 p.m.
                        tomorrow, Tuesday, April 6, at which he will give the press the text of the
                        stabilization plan for release in the morning papers of April 7.
                        [Welles.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>